@himanshug: for the interface changes, they are required in order to be able to pass in a custom url instead of just host & port for services. 
Another way to handle could be to add in another interface IntegrationTestingConfigV2 with a backwards compatible impl for wrapping up IntegrationTestingConfig to V2.
However the current approach seems more cleaner.

Okay, I see that could be a pain, if we want VirtualColumns to be able to return primitives too. What if we do these changes:

1) Add VirtualColumn with this interface:

```
public interface VirtualColumn
{
  String getOutputName();

  ObjectColumnSelector makeObjectColumnSelector(ColumnSelectorFactory factory);

  byte[] getCacheKey();
}
```

2) Remove `NumericColumnSelector makeMathExpressionSelector(String expression)` from ColumnSelectorFactory.

3) Add a MathExpressionVirtualColumn that makes ObjectColumnSelectors that return Numbers, solving the same use cases as "makeMathExpressionSelector" did.

That would make VirtualColumn the thing responsible for making generic (non-primitive, non-dictionary-encoded) derived columns out of some number of base columns.

In the future, if we want to get primitive selectors back too, we could add more "makeSelector" style methods to VirtualColumn.

This is what we are using currently.

```
public interface VirtualColumn extends Cacheable
{
  String getOutputName();

  ObjectColumnSelector asMetric(String dimension, ColumnSelectorFactory factory);

  FloatColumnSelector asFloatMetric(String dimension, ColumnSelectorFactory factory);

  DoubleColumnSelector asDoubleMetric(String dimension, ColumnSelectorFactory factory);

  LongColumnSelector asLongMetric(String dimension, ColumnSelectorFactory factory);

  DimensionSelector asDimension(String dimension, ColumnSelectorFactory factory);

  VirtualColumn duplicate();
}
```

